  "text": "The C system has been suggested to be involved in the pathogeneses of UC and CD, although differently. Thus, a putative auto-antigen, with a potential to initiate the classical pathway, is demonstrable in tissues affected by UC [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , whereas C activation may occur through the alternative pathway in patients with CD [CITATION_3] . The lectin-mediated C activation has not been considered in earlier studies of this topic.",
